book.armourers_workshop.guideBook.armour: The first thing you will need to get started building your custom armour is the armourer.§pAfter placing the block down right click it to open the GUI. Down the left side you will see all the types of equipment that can be build.

Select the type of equipment that you would like to crate then start building your equipment using Equipment Cubes.§pAfter you have finished place an equipment template into the armourer type in a name and press save.
book.armourers_workshop.guideBook.equipm: Equipment templates are what equipment skins are saved on simply place the equipment skin into the equipment wardrobe to apply the skin.
book.armourers_workshop.guideBook.introd: Note: This book is still a WIP.§pWelcome to the Armourer's Workshop Guide Book.§pThis book will help you get started with Armourer's Workshop.
Armourer's Workshop will let you build your own equipment skins for armour and weapons to replace their look!
book.armourers_workshop.guideBook.painti: A number of painting tool have been provided to help with your creative endeavour!§pColour Mixer§nAllows you to mix up any colour you like.§pPaintbrush§nPaints a single Equipment Cube.
Colour Picker§nLets you pick a colour from an Equipment Cube and set a Colour Mixer to that colour.§pPaint Roller§nPaints Equipment Cube's in a 3*3*1 area.
Burn Tool§nMakes an Equipment Cube darker.§pDodge Tool§nMakes an Equipment Cube lighter.§pColour Noise Tool§nApplies random colour noise to an Equipment Cube.
Shade Noise Tool§nApplies random shading to am Armour Cube.§pSome tools can be configured by sneaking and pressing right click.

inventory.armourers_workshop.global-skin: Você foi banido de hopedar visuais

Here you can join the Armourer's Workshop global skin library. Joining the global library will allow you to:
* upload your creations
* fill out your profile
* rate skins
* create lists of skins
* earn badges

Please read each page of the rules carefully. ignorance of the rules is not an excuse if you get banned.

Click the arrow on the buttom right to go to the next page.

The global library has a 3 strike rule, if you get 3 strikes your account will be permanently ban from uploading to the global library.

1. Do not upload other peoples work without their permission.
2. Do not abuse the report system.
3. Do not upload loads of coloured versions of the same model. (use dyes)
4. Do not upload adult content (sexual, drug use, etc)
5. Do not upload illegal content.

Derivative works are allowed on the global library. Please make sure any skins you upload from others are heavily edited and credited.\n\nBasic edits like recolours or settings changes are not allowed.
Please note that you must have a legitimate Minecraft account to join. This is to help with moderation and prevent spammers.

Ready to join? Click the button below to join the community!

If you have any issues joining please come by the Discord server for help.
